# Node.js Dependencies
# This folder contains all the downloaded packages. It's huge and can be
# perfectly recreated by running `npm install`. It MUST be ignored.
/node_modules

# Session Data & Sensitive Files
# This is critical for security. Your Instagram session file acts like a password.
# NEVER commit it to GitHub.
ig-session.json

# Environment Variables
# If you ever decide to use a .env file for local testing, this will prevent it
# from being committed. Credentials should always be in GitHub Secrets.
.env
.env.*

# Logs
# Ignore log files generated during runs or by npm on errors.
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log
yarn-error.log
*.log

# Temporary Image Output
# If your script ever saves the generated image locally before posting,
# this will ignore it.
*.jpeg
*.jpg
*.png

# Operating System Files
# Ignore junk files created by macOS, Windows, and Linux.
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
._*
ehthumbs.db

# IDE/Editor Configuration
# Ignore user-specific settings from editors like VS Code.
.vscode/
.idea/